  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"draven","win":["Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Draven","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Draven's Spinning Axe damage is brutal in this window and his E (Stand Aside) plus W (Blood Rush) speed let him run you down; your immobile body is prime prey, so never trade into caught axes."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Whirling Death) executes and his snowball economy off axe stacks means level 6 is another all-in threat you can't escape; play far back and deny his catches."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Draven's Blood Money lead lets him buy ahead, so even with Guinsoo online he can still out-item and one-combo you; the lane stays his."},{"when":"Late","text":"If you survive to 3+ items your %max-health W shred and attack speed out-scale Draven's front-loaded axe damage, which falls off; kited-safe you win the long game."}],"wants":{"you":["survive the early snowball to 3+ items","an enchanter to peel his run-downs and Stand Aside","deny axe stacks so his Blood Money never snowballs"],"foe":["catch axes and run you down with Blood Rush","snowball Blood Money gold off early kills","end before your late-game shred out-scales his axes"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are hard Draven; a single caught Spinning Axe hits like a truck and Blood Rush lets him close on your no-dash body, so respect his all-in and only farm safely.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 he keeps running you down with E knockaside and speed, snowballs axe-stack gold, and threatens a Whirling Death execute; hug tower and starve his catches.","late":"At first item he can still out-gold you, but by 3+ items your Bio-Arcane Barrage %HP shred and attack speed out-scale his front-loaded axe damage, so the long game and teamfights are yours if you stay alive.","whys":["A single caught Spinning Axe out-trades immobile Kog'Maw at level 1.","Blood Rush speed and axe damage let him run you down at level 2.","His snowball axe economy dominates the level 3-5 window.","No escape means he keeps catching you through levels 4-5.","Whirling Death execute makes his level-6 all-in lethal.","His Blood Money lead out-items you even at first item.","By 3+ items your %HP shred out-scales his front-loaded axes."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"ezreal","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ezreal spams Q (Mystic Shot) to poke and farm safely while E (Arcane Shift) lets him dodge any commit against your no-dash body; take the poke, farm, and wait out the lane."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Trueshot Barrage) adds chip and his Arcane Shift keeps him uncatchable, so he holds lane control; don't overextend into a gank with no escape of your own."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You flip here: Guinsoo's Rageblade brings W (Bio-Arcane Barrage) online and your sustained DPS beats his poke pattern before his Manamune-based scaling matters."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 3+ items your %max-health on-hits vastly out-DPS Ezreal's single-target poke; if your support peels his skillshots you win every extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["reach first item and Guinsoo online","peel to survive his poke and Arcane Shift kiting","force long fights where your DPS out-scales his pokes"],"foe":["poke you down with Mystic Shot before your spike","use Arcane Shift to dodge your all-ins","stall the lane and scale off Manamune"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favor Ezreal; Mystic Shot poke and Arcane Shift mobility let him chip and reposition safely against your immobile, short-range body, so soak XP and last-hit clean.","mid":"Through levels 3-5 he keeps poking with Q, dodging commits with E, and threatening Trueshot Barrage chip; you have no escape, so farm behind minions until your item spike lands.","late":"At first item your Bio-Arcane Barrage comes online and by 3+ items your %HP shred and attack speed hard out-DPS his single-target poke kit, flipping the lane and every teamfight when kept safe.","whys":["Ezreal's Mystic Shot poke and safety beat immobile Kog'Maw at level 1.","Arcane Shift mobility and Q poke keep him ahead at level 2.","Poke-and-dodge pattern dominates the level 3-5 window.","No escape means his kiting keeps punishing you through levels 4-5.","Trueshot Barrage chip and mobility hold his edge at level 6.","At first item Guinsoo brings your W online and you overtake his poke.","By 3+ items your %HP shred vastly out-DPS his single-target pokes."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Heimerdinger's spike, not yours: two or three H-28G turrets plus a W double-blast wall off the wave and chunk you whenever you step up to last-hit with your short base range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Heimerdinger stays ahead because R-upgraded turrets or the CH-3X E stun let his support commit an all-in before your Bio-Arcane Barrage range advantage matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still his window: one completed item on Heimer means his turret field out-DPSes you in lane and you cannot dive it without eating stun rockets."},{"when":"Late","text":"Finally yours: with Guinsoo/Runaan online, Bio-Arcane Barrage's %max-HP on-hit shreds his squishy body from a screen away and turrets can't chase you in a teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach two completed items so W's range and on-hit melt him from max distance","A hard-engage support to blow him up before he re-lays turrets","Neutral waves that let you farm safely until you outscale"],"foe":["A stacked turret field to zone you off the wave and CS","Early skirmishes at levels 2-6 while you're immobile and short-range","Poke you below tower dive range with W grenade and turret beams"]},"early":"You're the immobile one and Heimer owns level 1-2: he drops an H-28G turret on the wave and the beams zone you off every caster minion, while his W grenade pokes you the moment you walk up. Hug the tower, let melee minions tank the turret, and only last-hit with autos you can safely reach. Don't try to trade into the turret field, you have no range advantage yet and no escape.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Heimer-favoured. His turret carpet plus the E stun (or Q-stack burst) gives his lane the all-in, and your Void Ooze slow is your only peel. Ping your support to respect the CH-3X stun and never step past your minions into a triple-turret pocket. Farm from max auto range, use E to disengage if his support walks up, and just get to your items alive.","late":"Once your first item and especially two items land, the matchup flips to you. Bio-Arcane Barrage's bonus range and %max-health magic damage let you sit outside turret range and shred Heimer, who is a stationary squishy in fights. Space behind your frontline, let Q's attack-speed steroid stack your DPS, and blow him up before he can wall you off. This is your 59% territory, you just had to survive to it.","whys":["Level 1 is Heimer's: his H-28G turret and W grenade zone your short-range last-hitting immediately.","Level 2 stays Heimer's as a second turret and the wave push deny you safe CS.","Level 3 is Heimer's because the full turret field plus E outrange and out-poke your immobile body.","Levels 4-5 remain Heimer's as turret DPS and grenade poke keep you pinned under tower.","Level 6 is Heimer's since R-upgraded turrets or the CH-3X stun enable a support all-in before you spike.","First item is still Heimer's, one item can't beat a stacked turret field you can't dive.","Two-plus items is finally Kog'Maw's: W's range and on-hit shred him from safety while turrets can't chase in fights."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"jhin","win":["Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jhin's window: his fourth shot crit plus a W root off your support's tag deletes a huge chunk of your health, and you have no dash to dodge it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Jhin's: Curtain Call ults from off-screen threaten to execute you after lane trades, and his burst pattern beats your slow-ramp DPS in a 2v2."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jhin stays ahead on one item because his lethality burst one-combos your squishy immobile body before your on-hit ramps."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yours at last: with Guinsoo and attack-speed items, Bio-Arcane Barrage's uncapped range and %max-HP shred out-sustain Jhin's four-shot reload DPS in extended fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach two items so continuous on-hit DPS beats his four-shot reload","A peel/disengage support to survive his W root and R","Farm safely and avoid the fourth-shot crit trade window"],"foe":["Land the 4th-shot crit and W root to burst you before you ramp","Use Curtain Call to snipe you after skirmishes","Poke you with Q Dancing Grenade while you have no escape"]},"early":"Jhin controls level 1-2. His auto range and the fourth-shot guaranteed crit mean every trade favours him, and you're the immobile short-range one with no way to dodge. Last-hit from behind your minions, respect that his Q Dancing Grenade bounces off low minions onto you, and never contest a caster minion when he's holding his fourth shot. Take the farm you can reach safely and don't flip trades you can't win.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Jhin-favoured. His W Deadeye root off a support tag sets up a full burst combo that your slow-ramping kit can't answer, and at 6 Curtain Call threatens you from off-screen. Ward the flanks, hold Void Ooze to slow his reposition or peel a diving support, and don't step up into fourth-shot range. Play for even farm and get to your item spikes alive.","late":"Once two items are online the lane and teamfights become yours. Jhin's damage is front-loaded and capped by his reload, while Bio-Arcane Barrage gives you uncapped range and %max-health on-hit that grows the longer a fight runs. Space at the very back, let Q's attack speed stack your DPS, and melt him before he can finish a four-shot rotation. Survive to items and the 54% edge is yours.","whys":["Level 1 is Jhin's: superior range and the fourth-shot crit win every early trade.","Level 2 stays Jhin's as his Q bounce and auto poke chunk your immobile body.","Level 3 is Jhin's because the W root sets up burst you can't escape.","Levels 4-5 remain Jhin's as his lethality combo out-trades your slow ramp.","Level 6 is Jhin's since Curtain Call threatens to execute you after any trade.","First item is Jhin's, his front-loaded burst one-combos you before your on-hit spikes.","Two-plus items is Kog'Maw's: uncapped W range and %max-HP DPS out-sustain his capped reload damage."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"jinx","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Skill","Jinx","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jinx's window: her rockets (W-range Q swap) out-poke your short base range, and Zap slows you for a follow-up all-in you can't dash out of."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even: both ults are teamfight tools rather than lane executes, so level 6 comes down to who positions and spaces better in the 2v2."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jinx edges ahead again: her first item plus rocket range and Get Excited resets give her lane the all-in tempo over your slower ramp."},{"when":"Late","text":"A true skill matchup: both hyper-carries hit uncapped range, so it's decided by kiting, frontline, and who gets peeled better in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach uncapped W range and out-DPS her per-hit with %max-HP on-hit","A peel support so you can free-fire while she's kept off you","Even farm through the early rocket-poke phase"],"foe":["Use rocket range and Zap slow to poke and set up all-ins early","Snowball off a kill via Get Excited move-speed resets","Punish your immobility before your on-hit ramps"]},"early":"Jinx owns levels 1-2. Swapping to rockets gives her more effective range than your short base auto range, and every trade-up she takes chunks you while you're the immobile one. Last-hit conservatively behind minions, respect that Pow-Pow minigun stacks her attack speed if you let her free-hit, and don't walk into rocket range for a single CS. Farm safe and wait for your scaling.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay Jinx-favoured on her Zap slow plus rocket poke, but level 6 evens out to a skill check, both ults are fight tools, not lane executes, so it's about spacing and support play. Hold Void Ooze to slow her Zap follow-up or peel a diving support, ward for ganks since neither of you escapes, and trade only when her Zap is down. Get through this even and you're set up to scale.","late":"With items the matchup becomes a genuine skill duel. Both of you reach uncapped range, but Bio-Arcane Barrage's %max-health on-hit gives you an edge into any beefy frontline while Jinx's rockets clear and reset off kills. It comes down to kiting, who has the better peel, and who gets caught. Sit at max range, let Q's attack speed stack, and win the positioning game, that's why this reads as Skill late, not a hard loss.","whys":["Level 1 is Jinx's: rocket range out-reaches your short base auto range.","Level 2 stays Jinx's as rocket poke and minigun stacking beat your immobile trades.","Level 3 is Jinx's because Zap's slow sets up all-ins you can't dash out of.","Levels 4-5 remain Jinx's on continued rocket poke and slow pressure.","Level 6 is even/Skill: both ults are fight tools, so positioning decides it.","First item is Jinx's, her rocket range and Get Excited resets give her the all-in tempo.","Two-plus items is Skill: both hyper-carries reach uncapped range and kiting decides it."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"kaisa","win":["Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kai'Sa's window: Q Icathian Rain and W passive plasma stacks let her burst you in short trades while your slow-ramp DPS and immobility lose the exchange."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Kai'Sa's: R Killer Instinct plus her support's engage lets her dash on top of you and delete you before your on-hit matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kai'Sa stays ahead: one item and her evolves make her a mobile assassin that all-ins your stationary body."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yours decisively: Bio-Arcane Barrage's uncapped range and %max-HP on-hit out-range and out-DPS her, and a peel support keeps her off you in fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach two items so W range and on-hit shred her before she reaches you","A peel/CC support to punish her R dash-in","Farm safely and deny plasma-stack burst windows"],"foe":["Stack W plasma and burst with Q in short trades","Use R Killer Instinct to dash onto your immobile body","All-in at 6 with her support before you scale"]},"early":"Kai'Sa controls levels 1-2. Her Q Icathian Rain pokes and her W builds plasma stacks for a burst you can't dodge as the immobile short-range carry. Hug tower, last-hit from behind minions, and never let her free-stack plasma on you. Don't flip trades, she wins the early skirmish and your value is entirely in scaling.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Kai'Sa-favoured. Her plasma detonation burst plus R Killer Instinct at 6 lets her (or her support's engage) close the gap and delete you before Bio-Arcane Barrage ramps. Hold Void Ooze to slow her approach or peel, ward the flanks since her R makes ganks lethal, and only step up when her Q is down. Survive to items, that's the entire game plan here.","late":"Two items flip this hard, and it's your 59% matchup. Kai'Sa is a short-range assassin who has to dive in, while your W gives you uncapped range and %max-health on-hit that melts her the instant she appears. Space at the very back behind your frontline, let a peel support punish her R dash, and shred her before she lands a full combo. Get to your spikes alive and you win going away.","whys":["Level 1 is Kai'Sa's: Q poke and plasma stacking out-trade your immobile body.","Level 2 stays Kai'Sa's as plasma burst threatens you every short trade.","Level 3 is Kai'Sa's because her detonation combo beats your slow DPS ramp.","Levels 4-5 remain Kai'Sa's on continued plasma-stack burst pressure.","Level 6 is Kai'Sa's since R Killer Instinct lets her dash on top of you.","First item is Kai'Sa's, her mobility and evolves all-in your stationary body.","Two-plus items is Kog'Maw's: uncapped W range and %max-HP shred her before she reaches you."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"kalista","win":["Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kalista","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kalista's window: her Pierce spear poke and constant Hop kiting let her whittle you down while your immobile body can never disengage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Kalista's: Fate's Call plus her support gives her lane a strong all-in that pulls you out of position before you spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kalista stays ahead: rend stacks plus one item let her execute you in trades your slow-ramp DPS can't answer."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yours: Bio-Arcane Barrage's uncapped range and %max-HP on-hit out-DPS her per-spear damage, and she has to run in Hop range to hit you."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach two items so W range and %max-HP on-hit out-scale her rend","A peel support to punish her committal Hop and Fate's Call","Farm safely and avoid the spear-plus-rend trade windows"],"foe":["Kite with Hop while stacking Rend spears on you","Use Fate's Call to engage or reposition her support","Punish your immobility before your on-hit ramps"]},"early":"Kalista dominates levels 1-2. Every auto is a Pierce spear that pokes you, and her passive Hop lets her dance in and out while you, the immobile carry, can't retaliate or escape. Last-hit behind minions, respect that stacked spears plus a Rend burst chunk you fast, and don't walk up for CS into her kiting. Take safe farm and wait to scale.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Kalista-favoured. Her Hop mobility means she out-trades and out-positions you every time, and at 6 Fate's Call sets up a support all-in that yanks you or dives you. Hold Void Ooze to slow her when she commits a Hop, ward flanks, and only trade when her Rend has just been spent. Play even and get to your items, that's the plan.","late":"With two items the matchup swings to you, your 53% edge. Kalista is a per-spear DPS carry who must be in Hop range to deal damage, while Bio-Arcane Barrage gives you uncapped range and %max-health on-hit that out-scales her rend as targets get beefier. Space at the back behind your frontline, let a peel support punish her commitment, and shred her before she stacks enough spears. Survive to items and you take over.","whys":["Level 1 is Kalista's: Pierce spear poke and Hop kiting beat your immobile body.","Level 2 stays Kalista's as spear stacks and mobility out-trade you.","Level 3 is Kalista's because Hop lets her kite every exchange in her favour.","Levels 4-5 remain Kalista's on Rend burst and constant repositioning.","Level 6 is Kalista's since Fate's Call sets up a support all-in on you.","First item is Kalista's, rend plus one item executes you in trades.","Two-plus items is Kog'Maw's: uncapped W range and %max-HP out-scale her per-spear damage."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"karthus","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karthus's window: Q Lay Waste last-hits the wave and pokes you from range while E Defile zones you, and you have no way to close or dodge his casts."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still Karthus's: Requiem plus his support's setup threatens to execute you from across the map after any lane damage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Karthus stays ahead: one AP item makes his Q poke hurt enough to keep you off the wave and set up all-ins."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yours: Bio-Arcane Barrage's uncapped range and %max-HP on-hit let you sit outside E and delete his fragile body, and he can't run you down."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach two items so W range and on-hit shred him from outside Defile","A peel/engage support to punish his lack of mobility","Farm safely and stay above Requiem execute range"],"foe":["Poke with Q Lay Waste while zoning with E Defile","Set up a Requiem snipe after lane damage","Punish your immobility and short range with ranged casts"]},"early":"Karthus controls levels 1-2. His Q Lay Waste lets him contest CS and poke you at range without ever stepping up, and you're the immobile short-range one who can't punish him for it. Last-hit behind minions, respect that repeated Q hits add up fast, and don't walk into E Defile range for a single caster minion. Take safe farm and scale.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Karthus-favoured. His Q poke plus E zoning keep you off the wave, and at 6 Requiem threatens to execute you from anywhere the moment you're low from trades. Track your HP against his ult, ward flanks, and hold Void Ooze to slow an engaging support or peel. Don't overstay when you're chunked, just farm to your item spikes.","late":"Two items flip this to your 59% favour. Karthus is a stationary, fragile caster with no escape, while Bio-Arcane Barrage gives you uncapped range and %max-health on-hit to shred him from well outside E Defile. Space at the very back, let Q's attack speed stack your DPS, and blow him up before he can free-cast. He can't run you down and can't out-range you late, so survive the poke phase and the matchup is yours.","whys":["Level 1 is Karthus's: Q Lay Waste pokes and contests CS from range you can't answer.","Level 2 stays Karthus's as Q poke plus E zoning keep you off the wave.","Level 3 is Karthus's because Defile zones your immobile body off farm.","Levels 4-5 remain Karthus's on accumulating Q poke and E pressure.","Level 6 is Karthus's since Requiem threatens to execute you after any trade.","First item is Karthus's, one AP item makes his Q poke keep you pinned.","Two-plus items is Kog'Maw's: uncapped W range and %max-HP shred him from outside Defile."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian's spike, not yours: with Q Piercing Light through the caster minions plus his Passive double-shot after any ability, he shoves and pokes you off farm while you have no dash and short range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lucian's Culling turns a Relentless Pursuit engage into a full combo that can delete you; your Living Artillery only pokes and does nothing to save you if he E-dashes onto you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His first-item spike (Essence Reaver / Galeforce) still outpaces you here since he front-loads burst, but your Guinsoo's-Blade-of-the-Ruined-King on-hit ramp is starting to close the gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is your window: stacked Bio-Arcane Barrage bonus range plus %HP on-hit and attack speed lets you out-DPS Lucian from behind your frontline where his short E-dash range can't safely reach you."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2-3 items and a peeling support so you can free-fire with W range","Fights where minions or terrain block his E dash to you","Scaling into 5v5 teamfights where you sit at max range"],"foe":["An early all-in on cooldowns with Relentless Pursuit + Culling","A poke war levels 1-6 where his mobility dictates trades","Catching you before your on-hit items and W range come online"]},"early":"Respect Lucian at levels 1-2: his Passive double-tap and Q make every trade favour him, so last-hit at max range, hug your caster minions, and never walk up for a CS without vision of his E. Take the safe farm and concede the shove.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are his kill window. Once he has Q, W Ardent Blaze, and E Relentless Pursuit he can dash in, proc his Passive twice, and burst you before you kite out; hold your E Void Ooze slow to peel his dash and only step up when his E is down or your support has CC ready.","late":"With Guinsoo's and a Zeal item your W turns Lucian's short reach against him: stack Bio-Arcane Barrage, stand behind your frontline, and shred him with %max-HP on-hit before he can close the gap. In 5v5 your DPS at range now wins the extended fight he wants to make short.","whys":["Lucian's Passive double-shot and Q poke dominate the level 1 trade before you have any tools.","At level 2 his early Q or W lets him win the all-in for first blood pressure.","Level 3 gives Lucian his full Q-W-E kit to dash, poke, and shove while you have no escape.","Through levels 4-5 Lucian keeps the mobility and burst edge over your immobile, short-range body.","Lucian's level 6 Culling plus Relentless Pursuit is a real kill combo where your ult only pokes.","At one item Lucian still front-loads more burst than your on-hit ramp has yet delivered.","By two-plus items your stacked W range, attack speed, and %HP shredding finally out-scale Lucian."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Miss Fortune owns this phase: her Double Up bounce off a minion or your support pokes you for huge damage, and her Passive Love Tap punishes every step you take toward a CS while you have no dash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Bullet Time is a fight-ender in the 2v2; if her support lands CC she can channel it on you and your immobile Kog'Maw body gets deleted before your Living Artillery matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"MF's first-item spike with Passive Love Tap procs still out-trades you, but your Guinsoo's on-hit stacking is just beginning to swing the extended DPS race your way."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your window: with stacked Bio-Arcane Barrage range and %HP on-hit you out-range and out-sustain-DPS a MF who has to stand still to channel her ult, and you can W her down from safety."}],"wants":{"you":["Grouped teamfights where you free-fire at max W range while she's forced to channel","A support who peels the CC that sets up Bullet Time","Reaching two items so your sustained on-hit DPS overtakes her burst"],"foe":["A poke lane abusing Double Up bounces off minions and your body","An all-in level 6 with Bullet Time behind support CC","Snowballing the lane before your W range and items come online"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Miss Fortune: her Passive Love Tap makes alternating-target autos hurt and Double Up threatens a bounce, so don't walk up between minions. Last-hit conservatively at range, keep minions between you and her so Double Up can't chain to you cleanly.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are MF's poke-and-shove window. She'll Q off the caster minions to chunk you and use Strut movespeed to dodge your E Void Ooze; keep your E to peel engages, farm safe, and never contest a push where you'd eat a Double Up bounce plus Love Tap.","late":"Once you hit two items with Guinsoo's and attack speed, your W flips the range war. Miss Fortune must stand still to channel Bullet Time, so hold your E slow and Flash to punish her ult, then melt her with %max-HP on-hit from behind your frontline where her poke can't reach.","whys":["MF's Love Tap Passive and Double Up threat beat your toolless level 1.","At level 2 her early Q poke and auto harass control the trade for her.","Level 3 gives MF full Double Up bounces and Strut kiting over your immobile body.","Through levels 4-5 her burst poke and shove keep the lane pressure hers.","MF's level 6 Bullet Time behind CC is a 2v2 fight-ender you can't dash out of.","At one item her Love Tap-fueled burst still out-trades your ramping on-hit.","By two-plus items your stacked W range and %HP shredding out-DPS her stationary ult."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah dominates this phase: her W Jubilant Veil dodges your autos and W poke, and her Q Formless Blade extended melee range lets her all-in your immobile Kog'Maw once she E-dashes through a minion onto you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nilah's Apotheosis is a huge point-and-click pull plus heal-amp teamfight ult; in the 2v2 she can Slipstream in, ult, and her support cleans up before your Living Artillery does anything."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her first-item spike as a lifesteal-scaling bruiser-ADC still out-brawls you up close, but your on-hit W ramp is starting to punish her whenever she can't reach you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your window: Nilah is melee, so a maxed Bio-Arcane Barrage plus %HP on-hit shreds her from range while your support peels her E dash, and she can't Jubilant Veil-dodge sustained on-hit forever."}],"wants":{"you":["Max range poke and DPS where her melee auto range can't touch you","A peel support to stop her E Slipstream engage","Scaling to two items so on-hit shred beats her lifesteal sustain"],"foe":["An all-in level 3-6 with E dash, W dodge, and Q extended range","Level 6 Apotheosis to lock the 2v2 with her support","Any short-range brawl where her lifesteal and W outlast you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Nilah's: her Q gives her deceptive extended melee reach and she can W Jubilant Veil your poke, so never walk up to CS within her dash range. Farm at max distance, keep minions between you, and respect that she wants exactly the short trade you can't win.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are her hard kill window. With E Slipstream she dashes through minions onto you, Q extends her auto range, and W dodges your W and autos entirely; hold your E Void Ooze to peel her dash and don't step up unless her E is down and your support has CC ready.","late":"Once you have two items and stacked Bio-Arcane Barrage, being melee is Nilah's curse: sit behind your frontline and shred her with %max-HP on-hit before she closes. Save your E slow and lean on your support to peel her Slipstream, and her lifesteal can't outrace your sustained range DPS.","whys":["Nilah's Q reach and W dodge beat your toolless, immobile level 1.","At level 2 her early Q or W lets her control the short trade she wants.","Level 3 gives Nilah her E dash to all-in your escape-less body.","Through levels 4-5 her dash, dodge, and lifesteal keep the lane hers.","Nilah's level 6 Apotheosis locks the 2v2 alongside her support.","At one item her melee brawl and sustain still out-fight your ramping on-hit.","By two-plus items your W range and %HP shred punish her melee range and win late."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"samira","win":["Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Samira","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira owns this phase: her E Wild Rush dash off a minion or your support lets her close instantly, her W Blade Whirl blocks your W and auto poke, and she builds Style stacks brawling your immobile Kog'Maw."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Inferno Trigger is a full-reset threat: if her support lands CC she dashes in, ults, and your Living Artillery poke does nothing to stop the 2v2 delete on your escape-less body."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira's first-item spike with lifesteal keeps her out-brawling you in melee range, but your Guinsoo's on-hit ramp is beginning to punish her whenever she isn't glued to you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your window: Samira must be point-blank to combo, so maxed Bio-Arcane Barrage range plus %HP on-hit shreds her from behind your frontline, and her W only blocks projectiles for a moment, not your sustained DPS."}],"wants":{"you":["Max range free-fire where her melee combo can't reach","A support who peels or CCs her E Wild Rush and W window","Two items so on-hit shred overpowers her lifesteal brawl"],"foe":["A level 3-6 all-in with E dash into W block into Q burst","Level 6 Inferno Trigger behind support CC for a reset fight","Any short-range slugfest where her Style stacks and lifesteal win"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Samira: her Q and passive melee-range synergy want a close trade, and she can W Blade Whirl any early poke. Don't walk up to CS within her E dash range, keep minions between you, and take safe last-hits at max distance instead of contesting.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are Samira's kill window. E Wild Rush resets off minions and champs so she dashes onto you, W blocks your W and autos, and Q finishes; hold your E Void Ooze to slow her out of a reset chain, and never step up unless her E is used and your support has CC ready.","late":"By two items with Guinsoo's and attack speed your W punishes her melee range: sit behind your frontline and melt her with %max-HP on-hit before she can dash in. Save your E slow and lean on your support to break her Wild Rush chains, and her lifesteal can't outpace your range DPS.","whys":["Samira's Q range and W block beat your toolless, immobile level 1.","At level 2 her early damage and melee threat control the trade for her.","Level 3 gives Samira her E Wild Rush to dash onto your escape-less body.","Through levels 4-5 her dash resets, W block, and lifesteal keep the lane hers.","Samira's level 6 Inferno Trigger behind CC is a 2v2 reset delete.","At one item her lifesteal brawl still out-fights your ramping on-hit.","By two-plus items your W range and %HP shred out-DPS her point-blank kit and win late."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Senna controls this phase: her Q Piercing Darkness pokes and heals through minions, her extreme auto range out-spaces your short-range last-hits, and she farms souls off your CS while you have no way to punish her."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Dawning Shadow gives Senna a global shield-and-poke ult, but she's a support-carry with low steady DPS; her level 6 threatens utility more than a 2v2 delete, keeping this phase her poke edge rather than a hard kill spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your window opens: with a completed on-hit item and Bio-Arcane Barrage your sustained DPS overtakes Senna's low base attack speed, and once you close range her squishy soul-scaling body melts."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard-win: stacked W range plus %HP on-hit shreds Senna far faster than her autos or Q can trade, and her lack of self-peel means any time your support locks her down she dies."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching one item so your DPS overtakes her low attack speed","Closing range with support peel to punish her squishy body","Teamfights where you free-fire while she pokes for little sustained damage"],"foe":["A long-range poke lane with Q Piercing Darkness and root passive range","Zoning your short-range CS levels 1-5","Farming souls off your minions to out-scale before you itemize"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Senna's range: her autos and Q out-distance you, so accept you'll be poked and focus on safe max-range last-hits. Don't walk up to trade into her superior reach, hug your minions against her Q line, and just farm through the harass.","mid":"Levels 3-6 she keeps poking and collecting souls, but her damage stays low and single-target. Weather the Q chip, keep farming, and hold your E Void Ooze to peel her camp or your support's engage; by the end of this phase you're one item from flipping the lane in your favour.","late":"From your first item on you take over: your on-hit W out-DPSes Senna's slow autos, and once you or your support close the gap her squishy, self-peel-less body can't survive your %max-HP shredding. Space at max W range in fights and delete her whenever she steps up to poke.","whys":["Senna's long auto range and Q poke beat your short-range level 1.","At level 2 her reach and soul-farm harass keep the trade hers.","Level 3 gives Senna Q Piercing Darkness to poke and sustain over you.","Through levels 4-5 her range and scaling souls zone your CS.","Even at level 6 her utility ult adds little steady DPS, but her poke edge still holds the phase.","At one item your on-hit W overtakes Senna's low attack speed and you take the lead.","By two-plus items your W range and %HP shred hard-out-DPS her fragile body."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Seraphine controls this phase: her Q High Note pokes you for heavy damage at range, E Beat Drop roots or slows to set up her support, and her W shields and heals so your short-range trades never break even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Encore is a lane-and-teamfight-ending charm chain, but Seraphine plays as a mage-support with low auto DPS; her level 6 threatens CC-setup burst more than a solo 2v2 kill, so her poke-and-control edge still defines the phase."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your window opens: once you complete an on-hit item and Bio-Arcane Barrage your sustained DPS dwarfs her weak autos, and her mana-hungry poke can't kill you before you close and shred her."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard-win: maxed W range plus %HP on-hit melts Seraphine's squishy body far faster than her spells can trade, and any time your support blocks her E-into-R chain she simply dies to your DPS."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching one item so on-hit DPS overtakes her feeble autos","Dodging her E Beat Drop so her Encore setup never lands","Fights where you free-fire at W range while she pokes for little"],"foe":["A long-range mage poke lane with Q High Note and W sustain","Landing E Beat Drop to root you for her support's follow-up","Zoning your CS levels 1-5 before you itemize on-hit"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Seraphine's range and sustain: her Q out-pokes you and her W heals any trade, so don't walk up into her spells. Take safe max-range last-hits, hug your minions to block her Q line, and respect that a step forward can eat an E root that sets up her support.","mid":"Levels 3-6 she pokes with Q and threatens E Beat Drop into her support's CC, but her own damage stays spell-reliant and mana-limited. Sidestep her E, farm through the poke, and hold your E Void Ooze to peel the engage; by the end of this phase you're one item from taking the lane over.","late":"From your first item on you flip it: your on-hit W out-DPSes Seraphine's near-useless autos, and once you close range her squishy body evaporates to %max-HP shredding. Dodge her E, let your support break the E-into-Encore chain, and space at max W range to delete her in every fight.","whys":["Seraphine's Q poke and W sustain beat your short-range level 1.","At level 2 her range and shielding keep the trade in her favour.","Level 3 gives Seraphine Q, W, and E Beat Drop to poke and lock you.","Through levels 4-5 her poke and CC-setup zone your CS.","Even at level 6 her Encore adds control, not steady DPS, so her poke edge still holds the phase.","At one item your on-hit W overtakes her weak autos and you take the lead.","By two-plus items your W range and %HP shred hard-out-DPS her fragile body."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sivir owns these levels: her Boomerang Blade (Q) plus Ricochet (W) out-trade and out-push you, and her Spell Shield (E) eats your Caustic Spittle (Q) for free while giving her mana back. Hug the melee minions so her Q only clips you through the wave, and never spend Q into a raised Shield."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nothing changes on 6 for you; Kog'Maw's Living Artillery (R) is poke, not an all-in, and Sivir's On The Hunt (R) gives her lane a movement-speed engage/disengage you can't match. Play for CS and let her burn tempo shoving; your ult only matters as chip if she face-checks."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item flips it. A completed Guinsoo's or Kraken plus Bloodrazor turns your W attacks into percent-max-HP shreds that melt through anything Sivir builds, and she has no steroid to answer sustained DPS. Space behind your support and let stacked W attack speed do the work."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items Kog'Maw is one of the highest DPS carries in the game and Sivir is a utility waveclear ADC by comparison; in extended fights your W melts her whole team while she can only Shield one cast. Demand a peel support and never let her R-engage catch you flat-footed."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2 items and full W attack-speed uptime","A peel support (Lulu, Milio, Nami) to keep you kiting","Extended late fights where DPS out-scales her utility"],"foe":["Spam Q/W poke and Spell-Shield your Q for free trades","Use On The Hunt to force early skirmishes and picks","End lane before your bruiser items come online"]},"early":"Sivir controls levels 1-2: her Q+W push the wave into you and Spell Shield negates your Caustic Spittle, so play safe, last-hit under threat, and don't feed her a free E-block.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Sivir's; she waveclears and pokes with Boomerang while her Shield trades favourably, and neither of your level-6 ults changes the 2v2 in your favour, so farm and scale.","late":"Once your first bruiser item lands the matchup inverts (win[5-6] Kog'Maw): W's percent-HP shred and Kog'Maw's obscene 2-item DPS blow past Sivir's utility kit as long as you have peel to kite behind.","whys":["Sivir's Q+W wave control and Spell Shield dominate the level-1 trade.","At 2 she out-pushes and pokes you with Boomerang Blade while Shield blocks your Q.","Level 3 Ricochet and Shell uptime keep every trade in Sivir's favour.","Through 4-5 she shoves and pokes safely while you can only farm.","Level 6 On The Hunt gives her side the engage/disengage; your R is just poke.","At one bruiser item your W shred and DPS finally out-trade her utility.","With 2+ items Kog'Maw's sustained DPS hard-outscales Sivir's waveclear kit."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kog'Maw","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is an even scaling race decided by execution. Smolder's Super Scorcher Breath (Q) pokes and builds his stacks toward the 225-stack execute, while your Bio-Arcane Barrage (W) gives you range and shred; whoever hits their pattern cleaner wins. Deny his Q last-hits so his stack count stalls, and only W-trade when his Q is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both hit power spikes but neither dominates: Smolder's Mouthful of Fire (R) is a big AoE nuke plus dragon while your Living Artillery (R) answers as poke. Respect his R burst on you when you're low, and use your range to farm safely rather than force an even coinflip."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item edges ahead (win[5] Kog'Maw): a completed on-hit item with Bloodrazor gives you online percent-HP DPS before Smolder's stacked Q scaling fully snowballs. Force short kite trades here while your W attack speed spikes and his execute threshold is still far off."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late it's a true skill matchup again: fully-stacked Smolder Q executes and his R burst can delete you, but 2-item Kog'Maw shreds his whole team faster if you kite well. Whoever positions cleaner in the 5v5 wins, so demand peel and never get caught by his R engage."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny Smolder's Q last-hits to stall his stack count","Reach your first on-hit item and short kite-trades","A peel support so your DPS out-races his execute"],"foe":["Farm Q stacks safely toward the 225 execute","Land Mouthful of Fire burst on you when low","Scale evenly and win the late positioning coinflip"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are dead even (win Skill): both of you want to farm and scale, Smolder stacking Q while you set up W range, so trade only on his cooldowns and protect your CS.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay a skill matchup; his Q poke and stack growth race your W shred, and level 6 gives him R burst while you get R poke, so clean execution decides each trade.","late":"Your first item tips it briefly to you (win[5] Kog'Maw) via early on-hit DPS, but with 2+ items it's even again: stacked Smolder can execute you while your kited W melts him first, so positioning is everything.","whys":["Level 1 is a symmetric farm-and-scale start, purely execution-decided.","At 2 both trade on cooldowns with no kit edge either way.","Level 3 W-range versus Q-poke stays a coinflip on mechanics.","Through 4-5 his stacking and your shred race neck-and-neck.","Level 6 R burst versus R poke keeps the all-in even.","Your first on-hit item spikes your DPS before his execute matures.","With 2+ items stacked Smolder and kiting Kog'Maw are a true skill fight."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain oppresses this whole window as a bot-lane mage: his Nevermove (W) root and Death's Hand (Q) fan of bolts punish you for stepping up to farm, and every proc heals him back. Kog'Maw is a short-legged immobile stacking carry with no escape, so stay behind minions and never get clipped by a W landing behind you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 is Swain's kill window, not yours: Demonic Ascension (R) with the Vision of Empire pull threatens to lock you and drain you to death with support follow-up. Your Living Artillery (R) is only poke and won't save you from a landed root, so hold Flash for his W and don't fight into his ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even at one item Swain stays ahead (win[5] Swain): he builds tanky-AP and his sustained R drain plus CC out-durations a squishy early-item Kog'Maw. Use your W range to poke and farm from max distance rather than trying to duel through his heal."},{"when":"Late","text":"Only with 2+ items do you flip it (win[6] Kog'Maw): Kog'Maw's percent-max-HP W shred is the perfect answer to a stacked-HP battlemage, melting Swain far faster than his drain can heal, provided your support peels his root. Space at max W range and never facecheck into his W engage."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2+ items so W shred out-damages his drain","A peel/disengage support to deny his W root","Max-range W poke and farming from safe distance"],"foe":["Land Nevermove root to set up the all-in","Use R drain plus CC to out-sustain your early trades","Snowball the 2v2 before your late shred comes online"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Swain: his Q bolts and looming W root make stepping up to last-hit dangerous, so farm passively behind the wave and give no free roots.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are Swain's strongest window; W-root into Q/passive burst plus his R drain at 6 can outright kill immobile Kog'Maw, so respect every root and never fight into Demonic Ascension.","late":"Only at 2+ items does it flip to you (win[6] Kog'Maw): your percent-HP W shred hard-counters his stacked HP and melts him faster than he can drain, as long as you kite his root with peel.","whys":["Level 1 Swain zones your CS with Q bolts and root threat.","At 2 his W-root all-in and self-heal beat your immobile trades.","Level 3 gives him full combo pressure you can't answer.","Through 4-5 his sustain and CC keep the 2v2 his.","Level 6 Demonic Ascension is a kill threat, not a Kog'Maw window.","Even at one item his tanky-AP drain out-durations your squishy DPS.","With 2+ items your percent-HP W shred finally melts his stacked health."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Tristana","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tristana owns the early lane: Rocket Jump (W) plus Explosive Charge (E) gives her all-in burst and mobility you flatly lack, and she can leap on you the moment you step up to last-hit. Kog'Maw is immobile and short-ranged early, so stay behind your minions, respect her W range, and don't get caught with her E ticking on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 is Tristana's kill spike, not yours: Buster Shot (R) knockback finishes her E detonation combo and can blow you up with support CC. Your Living Artillery (R) is poke only and won't win the all-in, so hold Flash for her W-jump and never sit in E-detonation range at low HP."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Tristana stays ahead at one item (win[5] Tristana): her E-charge burst plus reset-jump snowballs a lead before your on-hit scaling matures. Farm from max W range, giving her nothing to jump onto, and wait for your second item."},{"when":"Late","text":"Only with 2+ items does it flip (win[6] Kog'Maw): Kog'Maw's sustained percent-HP W shred out-DPSes Tristana's burst-and-reset pattern in extended fights, since once she jumps in she must commit. Demand a peel support, punish her when W is down, and kite at max range."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 2+ items for sustained W-shred DPS","A peel support to punish her after she jumps in","Max-range farming that denies her a W target"],"foe":["Land Rocket Jump onto you to start the E combo","Use Buster Shot at 6 to secure the all-in kill","Snowball early leads before your on-hit scaling lands"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Tristana's: her W-jump plus E threat makes stepping up to CS risky for immobile Kog'Maw, so farm safe and never give her a jump-in trade.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay hers; E-charge burst and Rocket Jump reset let her all-in you, and level 6 Buster Shot is a kill combo, so respect her cooldowns and don't fight into a full E stack.","late":"Only at 2+ items does it flip to you (win[6] Kog'Maw): sustained W percent-HP shred out-damages her burst-reset pattern once she's committed, provided you kite at max range with peel.","whys":["Level 1 Tristana's W mobility and E threat zone your CS.","At 2 her jump-in burst beats your immobile trading.","Level 3 full E-charge combo out-damages you outright.","Through 4-5 her all-in mobility keeps the 2v2 hers.","Level 6 Buster Shot is a kill combo, not a Kog'Maw window.","At one item her E-reset snowball still out-tempos your scaling.","With 2+ items your sustained W shred out-DPSes her committed burst."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch controls the lane through threat: Ambush (Q) stealth lets him reposition for a Venom Cask (W) slow plus Deadly Venom stacks, and he can gank-assist his own lane by vanishing. Kog'Maw is immobile with no way to punish a stealth pivot, so ward the flanks, hug minions, and don't chase a Twitch who walks into fog."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 is Twitch's spike, not yours: Spray and Pray (R) turns his stacked poison into piercing AoE that shreds you and your support through minions. Your Living Artillery (R) is only poke, so back off when his stacks are high and never group tightly with your support into his ult angle."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Twitch stays ahead at one item (win[5] Twitch): a completed crit or on-hit item plus his R makes his stealth-engage burst lethal before your DPS out-scales. Farm from max W range, keep pink wards down, and refuse to fight when he's unaccounted for."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late it becomes a true skill matchup (win[6] Skill): both are hyper-carry DPS ADCs, but Kog'Maw's percent-HP W shred out-trades in a straight fight while Twitch wins if his stealth flank catches you. Whoever positions cleaner in the 5v5 takes it, so demand peel and vision to deny his Q pick."}],"wants":{"you":["Vision on flanks to deny Twitch's stealth engage","Reach 2+ items so W shred wins a straight duel","A peel support to survive his R burst window"],"foe":["Use Q stealth to reposition for W-slow all-ins","Stack Deadly Venom then pop Spray and Pray on the group","Catch you flat-footed with an unwarded flank"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Twitch: his Q stealth and W-slow threat let him dictate trades while immobile Kog'Maw can't punish a fog pivot, so ward and farm cautiously.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Twitch's; stacked poison plus stealth engages and his level-6 R burst through minions can delete you, so respect his stack count and keep vision honest.","late":"With 2+ items it evens out to a skill matchup (win[6] Skill): your W percent-HP shred out-DPSes him in a fair fight, but his stealth flank still punishes bad positioning, so vision and peel decide it.","whys":["Level 1 Twitch's stealth and slow threat let him dictate the lane.","At 2 his Q-repositioning W-slow trades beat your immobility.","Level 3 stacked poison and stealth pressure keep it his.","Through 4-5 he controls tempo with fog pivots you can't answer.","Level 6 Spray and Pray burst through minions is his kill spike.","At one item his stealth-engage crit burst still out-tempos you.","With 2+ items it's a true skill fight: your shred versus his flank."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus rules the early lane with range and poke: charged Piercing Arrow (Q) plus Blighted Quiver (W) stacks and Hail of Arrows (E) zone you off the wave and chunk you before your W range comes online. Kog'Maw is immobile and short-legged here, so last-hit behind minions, dodge Q charges laterally, and don't stand in his E puddle to CS."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 still favours Varus in the 2v2: Chain of Corruption (R) is a lockdown engage that lets his support all-in an immobile carry with no escape. Your Living Artillery (R) is just poke and won't answer his R-catch, so hold Flash for the root and never step into Q range at low HP."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item flips it (win[5] Kog'Maw): a completed on-hit item with Bloodrazor turns your W into percent-HP shred, out-DPSing Varus's front-loaded poke once his blight combo is on cooldown. Force short kite-trades right after he uses Q/E and let attack speed win the exchange."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items Kog'Maw clearly out-scales (win[6] Kog'Maw): your sustained W shred melts anything in extended fights while Varus is a burst-poke carry who falls off in raw DPS. Space at max W range behind peel, punish his R being down, and don't get chain-rooted onto the frontline."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach your first on-hit item for W percent-HP shred","Short kite-trades right after his Q/E cooldowns","A peel support to deny his Chain of Corruption catch"],"foe":["Poke with charged Q and blight-stack detonations early","Use R root to set up the immobile-carry all-in","Win before your on-hit scaling out-DPSes his poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Varus's: his Q range and blight poke zone immobile Kog'Maw off CS, so farm safe behind minions and dodge his charged arrows.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Varus-favoured through poke and his level-6 R lockdown, which enables a support all-in on you, so respect the root and trade only on his cooldowns.","late":"Your first item flips it (win[5-6] Kog'Maw): W percent-HP shred and 2-item sustained DPS out-scale his front-loaded poke, so kite at max range with peel and punish his blight combo being down.","whys":["Level 1 Varus's Q range and E zone control your CS.","At 2 his charged-Q and blight poke out-trade your short range.","Level 3 full blight-detonation combo keeps trades his.","Through 4-5 his poke chunks you before your W scaling lands.","Level 6 Chain of Corruption enables an all-in on immobile you.","At your first on-hit item W shred out-DPSes his front-loaded poke.","With 2+ items your sustained shred hard-outscales his burst kit."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Vayne","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Neither of you wants this stage: Vayne's Tumble-empowered auto and Silver Bolts third-hit true damage hurt, but her range is only 550 and yours with Bio-Arcane Barrage active reaches out past hers, so respect Q Caustic Spittle's attack-speed steroid and poke her off the wave from a screen away while last-hitting safely behind your caster minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is Vayne's window: Final Hour gives her bonus AD, faster Tumble resets, and invisibility on Condemn stun-walls, letting her all-in through your slow reload. If her support has any hard CC you simply die, so hug tower and keep E Void Ooze up as a self-peel slow the moment she Tumbles onto you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once your first item lands (Guinsoo's or berserker-into-crit path) the duel flips back to a skill check; your W range and Q shred out-DPS her from max distance if you never let Condemn pin you to a wall. Space so a minion or open ground is always behind you."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items and Living Artillery chip you win any drawn-out fight, but Vayne's Final Hour uptime in extended teamfights is her equalizer. Position at the very back, let your support screen Condemn, and never be the closest target when she blinks in."}],"wants":{"you":["Open ground or minions behind you so Vayne's Condemn can't wall-stun","A peel support (Lulu, Milio, Braum) to screen her Q and Final Hour dive","Long fights where Bio-Arcane Barrage and Living Artillery out-range her 550"],"foe":["A wall behind you to Condemn-stun and burst you","Hard-CC engage support to lock you during her slow reload","Short brawls at 6 under Final Hour before your first item spikes"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a genuine coin-flip: her Tumble auto trades hurt but you out-range her the instant W is up, so poke with empowered autos and farm safely rather than committing.","mid":"Through 3-5 it stays a skill matchup on kiting and Q uptime, but at 6 Vayne's Final Hour plus Condemn all-in is the real threat window; sit on tower, save E to slow her Tumble, and don't get walled.","late":"Post first-item and into 2+ items you reclaim the DPS lead with W range and Living Artillery, provided you back-line perfectly and let your support answer her engage.","whys":["Level 1 is even because both of you just last-hit and neither auto range meaningfully bullies the other yet.","Level 2 stays a skill check as her Tumble trade and your empowered W poke roughly cancel out.","Level 3 is even because Q's attack-speed steroid answers her Silver Bolts DPS at max spacing.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-dependent on whether you kite her Tumbles or she catches a Condemn wall.","At Level 6 Vayne is ahead: Final Hour plus invisible Condemn all-ins beat your slow Living Artillery reload.","At first item it re-evens as your W range and crit spike restore parity in the duel.","With 2+ items it returns to a skill check because her Final Hour uptime offsets your scaling if she gets on you."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Veigar bot is played as a burst mage support-lane: his Baleful Strike Q pokes you for big chunks at 900+ range and stacks AP off last hits, badly out-ranging your auto game before W is fully online. Farm under tower, use minions to body-block Q, and only step up to last-hit when his Q is on cooldown, because you are the immobile target he most wants to blow up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Primordial Burst plus Event Horizon cage is a near-guaranteed kill on an unmobile Kog'Maw: if his W Dark Matter and R land while you're stunned you evaporate. Never walk into the E cage radius, keep Flash up, and don't take the reload window near him without vision of his cooldowns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where you climb ahead: once your first item completes, Bio-Arcane Barrage plus Q shred let you shove waves faster than he can poke, and if his Q or cage is down you out-DPS him hard. Play around his Event Horizon cooldown and start punishing every whiffed cage."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items you comfortably win: Living Artillery sieges from beyond his cast range and your sustained DPS shreds him if he ever mispositions. He remains a one-shot threat, so stand behind frontline and never be catchable by a flanking cage before you delete his team."}],"wants":{"you":["Minions between you and Veigar to eat Baleful Strike Q poke","A first-item spike to out-shove his poke and punish cage cooldowns","Flash and back-line spacing so Event Horizon never catches you"],"foe":["To poke you down with 900-range Q while you can't retaliate","A landed Event Horizon cage into W and Primordial Burst combo","Any pick where you're stunned during your slow reload window"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favor Veigar: his Baleful Strike Q out-ranges you and chunks you while you're forced to farm passively behind minions.","mid":"Through 3-6 he keeps the edge with poke stacking AP and the Level 6 cage-into-ult one-shot; block Q with minions, dodge Event Horizon, and never reload in his range.","late":"From first item onward you flip it: superior wave clear and Bio-Arcane DPS let you punish every cage cooldown, and with 2+ items you out-scale him outright while respecting his burst.","whys":["Level 1 Veigar is ahead because his Q already out-ranges and pokes your last-hitting.","Level 2 stays his as Baleful Strike stacks AP and chunks you with no answer.","Level 3 favors Veigar since his poke range still dominates before your W spike matters.","Levels 4-5 are his because stacked Q plus cage threat keeps you pinned under tower.","Level 6 is Veigar's biggest window: cage into Dark Matter and Primordial Burst one-shots an immobile you.","At first item you pull ahead as your wave clear and W DPS out-shove and punish his cage cooldowns.","With 2+ items you're clearly ahead because your scaling DPS beats his poke once you avoid the cage."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Kog'Maw","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah bullies the early game: her Double Daggers Q and Deadly Plumage W give her a strong ranged trade with feather DPS while you're the immobile, low-range target before W comes online. Farm safely behind your caster minions, respect her feather zoning near the wave, and use Q Caustic Spittle's attack-speed shred only when you can retreat, because her recall of blades hurts in extended trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Featherstorm is a clean disengage-and-untargetable ult that lets her dodge your Living Artillery and reposition for a Bladecaller root. If her support engages while her feathers are stacked behind you, the root chain can pin you through your reload, so hold E Void Ooze as a peel slow and don't stand on planted feathers."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is the turning point: once Bio-Arcane Barrage and your first crit/attack-speed spike land, your max-range sustained DPS out-trades her feather windows if you never eat a full Bladecaller root. Space behind minions and force her to commit feathers before you step up."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items you out-scale her: Living Artillery sieges from beyond her range and your W shreds tanks she can't. Her Featherstorm still buys her a dodge and her root threatens your positioning, so back-line hard and let your support screen the Bladecaller angle before you unload."}],"wants":{"you":["Minions in front so Xayah must commit feathers before rooting you","A first-item spike to out-range her feather-DPS trade windows","A peel or disengage support to answer Bladecaller root chains"],"foe":["Early feather trades with Double Daggers and Deadly Plumage while you're short-ranged","A landed Bladecaller root during your slow reload window","Featherstorm to dodge Living Artillery and reset an all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 go to Xayah: her Q and feather DPS give her the stronger short-range trade before your W range comes up.","mid":"Through 3-6 she keeps zoning you with feathers and threatens root all-ins, capped by Featherstorm at 6; farm behind minions, dodge the Bladecaller angle, and save E to peel.","late":"From first item on you take over as your W range out-trades her feather windows, and with 2+ items you out-scale her outright while respecting her root and ult dodge.","whys":["Level 1 Xayah is ahead because her Double Daggers give her a stronger auto-and-feather trade.","Level 2 stays hers as Deadly Plumage DPS out-trades your short pre-W range.","Level 3 favors Xayah since feather zoning controls the wave and your last-hitting.","Levels 4-5 remain hers with root-threat all-ins while you're immobile.","Level 6 is Xayah's because Featherstorm dodges your artillery and sets up her root engage.","At first item you flip ahead as your W range out-DPSes her feather windows.","With 2+ items you're clearly ahead because your siege and tank shred out-scale her kit."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri out-mobilities and out-pokes you early: her Q machine-gun autos poke through minions at range and her E wall-dash makes her impossible to pin, while you're the slow, immobile farmer. Sit behind your caster minions, use Q Caustic Spittle's shred only in safe windows, and don't overstep to CS, because she kites your every step and chunks you with sustained Q poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lightning Crash turns her into a hyper-mobile skirmisher that resets on takedowns and overcharges her move speed and attack speed, letting her dive or kite you off your reload freely. You have no escape, so hold E Void Ooze to peel her dash-in and never fight without your support's CC ready to stop her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Zeri spikes hard on her first crit/attack-speed item too, so this stays her window rather than yours: her scaling ramps as fast as yours while she keeps the mobility edge. Farm even, avoid extended trades where her Q DPS plus dash uptime beats your positioning, and play for scale."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is where you finally pull ahead: with 2+ items Living Artillery and Bio-Arcane Barrage give you longer effective range and heavier tank shred than her Q, and in a 5v5 your peeled back-line DPS out-damages her if she can't freely dive. Stand behind frontline, let your support wall her dash angle, and out-range her."}],"wants":{"you":["A 2+ item teamfight where your W range and tank shred out-scale her Q","A peel/CC support (Nautilus, Leona) to lock her mobility down","Minions and back-line spacing so she can't kite you off reload"],"foe":["Early lane where her Q poke and E dash out-trade your immobile farming","Lightning Crash uptime to kite and dive you at will","Open skirmishes before your 2-item spike where her mobility dominates"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favor Zeri: her Q poke through minions and E mobility let her chip you while you can only farm safely.","mid":"Through 3-6 she keeps dominating with kite poke and the Lightning Crash mobility spike; hug tower, hold E to peel her dash, and don't fight without support CC.","late":"Only with 2+ items do you take over, as your W range, Living Artillery siege, and tank shred out-scale her Q in a peeled teamfight.","whys":["Level 1 Zeri is ahead because her Q pokes through minions while you can't retaliate.","Level 2 stays hers as her E mobility and Q DPS control the trade.","Level 3 favors Zeri since her kite pattern chips you off every CS attempt.","Levels 4-5 remain hers with sustained poke and untouchable dash spacing.","Level 6 is Zeri's because Lightning Crash's mobility and resets let her dive or kite you freely.","At first item she keeps the edge as her scaling ramps just as fast while she holds the mobility advantage.","With 2+ items you finally pull ahead because your W range and siege out-scale her in a peeled fight."]},
  {"a":"kogmaw_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Kog'Maw"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs bot is a poke-mage lane: his Bouncing Bomb Q chunks you from way outside your auto range and Satchel Charge W zones you off the wave, so you're forced to farm passively as the immobile target he loves. Body-block Q with minions, only step in to last-hit when his Q is down, and never let his W knock you into a bad spot during your slow reload."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Mega Inferno Bomb gives him global execute pressure and lane burst; combined with Q poke he can push you off tower and threaten your reload from a screen away. Keep W Bio-Arcane range as your retaliation, but respect that his artillery still out-ranges your early autos, so trade only when his Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is the even point of the lane: once your first item lands your wave clear matches his and your W DPS lets you punish any Satchel or Q cooldown, but his poke is still relevant so it's a genuine skill check on who lands cooldowns. Shove with W, hold E to peel his all-in, and play the poke war patiently."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items you take over: Living Artillery answers his siege from equal range while Bio-Arcane Barrage gives you the sustained team-fight DPS and tank shred he simply lacks. Stand behind frontline out of Q range, force him to waste Satchel, and out-damage him in any extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["A first-item spike to match his wave clear and punish Q/Satchel cooldowns","2+ items where your sustained W DPS and siege out-scale pure poke","Minions and back-line spacing to eat Bouncing Bomb Q poke"],"foe":["Early lane where Bouncing Bomb Q out-ranges and pokes you down","Satchel Charge zoning to push you off farm during reload","Mega Inferno Bomb execute pressure while you're immobile"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favor Ziggs: his Q out-ranges your autos and pokes you while you farm passively behind minions.","mid":"Through 3-5 he keeps poking and zoning with Q and Satchel, capped by his global ult; block bombs with minions and only trade on his cooldowns.","late":"By first item the lane evens into a skill check on landing cooldowns, and with 2+ items you pull ahead as your sustained W DPS and Living Artillery out-scale his poke.","whys":["Level 1 Ziggs is ahead because his Bouncing Bomb Q out-ranges and pokes your last-hitting.","Level 2 stays his as Q poke and Satchel zoning keep you passive.","Level 3 favors Ziggs since his artillery range still dominates before your W matters.","Levels 4-5 remain his with sustained poke pushing you off the wave.","Level 5 continues Ziggs-favoured because his Q chip and Satchel keep you pinned under tower.","At first item it evens into a skill check as your wave clear matches his and you punish cooldowns.","With 2+ items you're ahead because your sustained W DPS and siege out-scale his pure poke."]}
